title: Google\Cloud\AIPlatform\V1\TimestampSplit
name: TimestampSplit
description:
Assigns input data to training, validation, and test sets based on a provided timestamps. The youngest data pieces are assigned to training set, next to validation set, and the oldest to the test set.

Supported only for tabular Datasets.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.aiplatform.v1.TimestampSplit

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.training_fraction
params.description: The fraction of the input data that is to be used to train the Model.

params.name: data.validation_fraction
params.description: The fraction of the input data that is to be used to validate the Model.

params.name: data.test_fraction
params.description: The fraction of the input data that is to be used to evaluate the Model.

params.name: data.key
params.description: Required. The key is a name of one of the Dataset's data columns. The values of the key (the values in the column) must be in RFC 3339 date-time format, where time-offset = "Z" (e.g. 1985-04-12T23:20:50.52Z). If for a piece of data the key is not present or has an invalid value, that piece is ignored by the pipeline.
